<span id="freeTextContainer12846098837223321419">Best stories do not have an ending<br/><br/>An Alien Empire before humankind? An urban legend or a hidden truth?<br/>Are we &quot;completely&quot; human? &quot;Human&quot; as far as our science has discovered till today and as far as our written memories, that we call history, could remember.<br/>There are some theories that reveal mysteries that we feel them like part of ourselves, like something we should know, but we don&apos;t anymore.<br/>In this book, the author tells a story of an ancient earth chronicles according to Zecharia Sitchin&apos;s </span>
  <span id="freeText12846098837223321419" style="display:none">Best stories do not have an ending<br /><br />An Alien Empire before humankind? An urban legend or a hidden truth?<br />Are we "completely" human? "Human" as far as our science has discovered till today and as far as our written memories, that we call history, could remember.<br />There are some theories that reveal mysteries that we feel them like part of ourselves, like something we should know, but we don't anymore.<br />In this book, the author tells a story of an ancient earth chronicles according to Zecharia Sitchin's theory, mixed with the modern human chronicles, that makes the reader part of a humanity that awakes to the truth about its origins and part of those human beings that realize that this ancient truth could change their lives.<br /><br />Best stories do not have an ending, but they continue in our thoughts, and they continue to live around us.<br />This book tells one of these stories. </span>
