<div id="review_1086802161" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1086802161" />
    <a title="Jannelle" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/22172154-jannelle"><img alt="Jannelle" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1086802161?book_show_action=true">Oct 22, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jannelle" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jannelle" href="/user/show/22172154-jannelle">Jannelle</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1086802161" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer48658198837747697"><strong>Nice idea, poorly executed.</strong><br/><br/>To me, the book comes across as juvenile. The wording is awkward. There is the impression that it was written by a preteen. It is more of a child&apos;s daydream than a serious book. Phrases like, &quot;at top speed, only to return faster.&quot; and the over use of the word &quot;indeed&quot;. Can not recommend this book for young adults because it teaches poor writing. Can&apos;t believe the good reviews it has. I definitely disagree.</span>
  <span id="freeText48658198837747697" style="display:none"><strong>Nice idea, poorly executed.</strong><br /><br />To me, the book comes across as juvenile. The wording is awkward. There is the impression that it was written by a preteen. It is more of a child's daydream than a serious book. Phrases like, "at top speed, only to return faster." and the over use of the word "indeed". Can not recommend this book for young adults because it teaches poor writing. Can't believe the good reviews it has. I definitely disagree.</span>
